[R1] {'review_id': 'CfiKcNa0W6TRoKrMn5cufA', 'user_id': 'D7tKvZrrXV6u0IMPxLE01A', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Don't pass this one by! Quaint, quiet, foodie spot with personality. Premier service and dedication to the craft of providing you with a taste not to be forgotten. We will be back and often!", 'date': '2021-12-15 04:22:04', 'user': {'name': 'Michael', 'review_count': 13, 'yelping_since': '2012-01-25 03:59:23', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.69, 'fans': 0}}
[R2] {'review_id': 'hN7VDDam7-0dqrnJk2PcuQ', 'user_id': 'i8kLw9NZv7l-Iyz1Y4VMbg', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'Our party of 4 had dinner reservations at 6:00pm and were promptly seated when we arrived. The place was already buzzing with activity with most of the tables filled with dinner guests. The service was impeccable with our BYOB wine being uncorked, water glasses filled and a basket of fresh crusty Italian bread with dipping olive oil arriving at our table within minutes of being seated. The menu is extensive with many interesting Italian specialties. Only a seasoned chef can handle so many wonderful dishes on a daily basis! In most eateries a couple of these dishes would be offered only as the dinner special. So, we started with Polipo Fantasia which is grilled octopus with capers, puréed ceci beans and sun dried tomatoes, finished with olive oil and balsamic glaze. The octopus was grilled to perfection and the puréed chick beans was fabulous. Not a humus but a delicious dipping sauce. A second appetizer plate was Calamari Fritti which is traditional fried calamari but these were served in a sweet and spicy chili sauce. A really great mixtures of flavor between the sweet & spicy but adding to the explosion of flavor were the fried calamari. The calamari were crisp, tender and not chewy or greasy! The final appetizer plate was Antipasto which is Chef Tony\'s selection of an assortment of Italian specialty meats, cheese, and vegetables that included thinly sliced soppressata, salami, prosciutto, provolone, pecorino and mozzarella cheeses, pickled eggplant, roasted peppers, fresh and sundried tomatoes...yep another culinary delight! Some in our party had eaten here before and knew their go to pasta dish was Fettuccine Pugliese that\'s squid ink fettuccine with shrimp and crab meat, served in a cheese bowl with white wine sauce. I tried Gnocchi Mascarpone con Aragosta which is mascarpone gnocchi sautéed with lobster and typically finished with a touch of tomato and cream, but I skipped the tomato and cream and the Chef accommodated my request for an arrabiata sauce. Each gnocchi was stuffed with a dab of mascarpone and cooked to perfection! For my taste the lobster in arrabiata sauce was heaven! All four pasta plates were sparkling clean from our "scarpetta." The dinner was topped off with espressos and orders of strawberry and hazelnut gelatos! This is a must discover place for the foodies of Philadelphia!', 'date': '2021-11-06 12:27:37', 'user': {'name': 'Tony', 'review_count': 59, 'yelping_since': '2011-11-30 16:33:35', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.25, 'fans': 0}}
[R3] {'review_id': 'EmHpPu3qaW7OgXCnwrST9w', 'user_id': 'qzATXHI4B34WVBRhovr8lg', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "$115 of pure disappointment. We ordered the caprese salad to start, which was their special of the night. The mozzarella and tomato were flavorless. If you've ever had fresh mozzarella, and I'm talking FRESH, the taste is a creamy melt in your mouth goodness. This was not it. We ordered another special of the night that was even worse than our starter; the veal was gray, slathered with a white gelatinous sauce--a texture that suggested the sauce might have been canned. We also ordered the Antonio pizza, which is topped with prosciutto, arugula, and oil. It was the driest pizza I've ever eaten. Giving them one last shot, we ordered the pistachio cake for dessert. The pistachio cake seemed to be an angel-like cake with cannoli filling. On brand with the rest of our meal, the pistachio cake left more to be desired; it simply lacked flavor. The only thing we enjoyed was the wine we brought with us.", 'date': '2021-10-17 20:32:24', 'user': {'name': 'Sabrina', 'review_count': 13, 'yelping_since': '2015-01-10 06:23:34', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.92, 'fans': 0}}
