[R26] {'review_id': 'NRXCPAcdMC4BFKMNen6PpQ', 'user_id': 'zGLOqw97kcJh2-LZoa4zbQ', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We went to this spot for outdoor dining during COVID.  We had the caprese salad, octopus appetizer, broccoli rabe and sausage appetizer, branzino special, truffle pasta and the espresso bar dessert.  The food was amazing, and the service was phenomenal.  We will definitely be back.', 'date': '2020-08-29 19:03:30', 'user': {'name': 'Maggie', 'review_count': 6, 'yelping_since': '2016-01-30 01:02:55', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.17, 'fans': 0}}
[R27] {'review_id': 'NpFPunEWbpDiQICkEgDpbA', 'user_id': 'yBQ1VOFV6LTRzSdTJYU0Hw', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I am not a dessert person (or try not to be) but the lemon cake in the summer is hands down one of the best that I have ever had!!! If dining outside-the grilled octopus is a new fave and of course the caprese salad and gnocchi!', 'date': '2020-08-20 11:45:03', 'user': {'name': 'Leyla', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2018-09-24 22:42:55', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.75, 'fans': 0}}
[R28] {'review_id': '2WJn3PTRvT3L6EJ8o1FQ_Q', 'user_id': '-edtYchmqsWXcatl_NjuKw', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Wonderful little Italian BYOB. The staff was very friendly and genuine. The food was delivered quickly and was so delicious it was devoured almost as fast. First time at Ristorante Aroma and will not be the last; definitely going to be added to the rotation and will spread the word. The food was that good. You can't beat the quality of the food for the price and a BYOB to boot. Low key one of the best Italian spots in the city.", 'date': '2020-02-15 00:53:17', 'user': {'name': 'Michael', 'review_count': 13, 'yelping_since': '2013-06-17 23:29:44', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.54, 'fans': 0}}
[R29] {'review_id': 'ZwtcIS2xFbNmxMgFG47u1g', 'user_id': 'NxI3Xy5Lj94g3CdhGL9SeQ', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I love this place! This is my go to Italian spot in the city. The service is 5 stars, Giulio is an incredible server who is knowledgeable, attentive, and always makes dinner more enjoyable with his witticisms. I have never felt rushed here but have also never waited for my dish. Though I've tried many items on the menu and never left disappointed, I now have my favorites (app: prosciutto, meal: gnocchi marscapone, dessert: hot and cold). It's also a BYOB so you really can't beat it. I enjoy coming here for intimate meals, date nights, with friends, and have even thrown a birthday party here. They do it all and have always made sure it was an incredible experience. I can't rave about this place more. If you haven't tried this place out yet, make sure you do! It is well worth it.", 'date': '2020-02-06 13:04:35', 'user': {'name': 'Lauren', 'review_count': 11, 'yelping_since': '2017-03-03 19:01:23', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.92, 'fans': 0}}
[R30] {'review_id': '-WPWNF7eJ3xq0YONFKkWvA', 'user_id': 'w-SQkxtXDZ48mxOC6hFnAg', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'The BEST Italian in Philly. A hidden gem! Giulio is knowledge, friendly and attentive. The branzino was delicious and the presentation was amazing. Do not sleep on this place!!!', 'date': '2020-01-17 01:56:01', 'user': {'name': 'Jennifer', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2015-10-17 23:44:38', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R31] {'review_id': '_E4EVn6q6VoyyHnHDWoA-w', 'user_id': 'V0BpQWRsBKasV288vayqbA', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "At Ristorante Aroma, I didn't just get a meal; I got an experience. It's rare to find a restaurant with both authentic, incredible food AND fantastic, thoughtful service. I was the first to arrive out of my party. My two friends were running 30 minutes later than our reservation, so I was nervous that, because the restaurant is pretty small, we would lose the reservation. But the host chatted with me and kept my wine glass full until they arrived. Our waiter, Julio, was so charismatic and provided great recommendations. The Melanzane Involtini (the eggplant appetizer) was absolutely delicious, and we ended up all splitting a dessert (I wish I remembered what it was called - some sort of cookie/brookie type of thing with gelato on top. I died and went to heaven). We stayed in the restaurant just chatting with the waitstaff for literally four hours. They were so kind, friendly, and genuinely just wanted us to enjoy our dinner to the max. It probably helped that one of my friends spoke Italian. This was one of my favorite, most heart-warming experiences at a restaurant to date. And for a BYOB in Philly, HIGHLY recommend. I hope to come back one day soon.", 'date': '2020-01-16 16:46:03', 'user': {'name': 'Kristen', 'review_count': 1, 'yelping_since': '2020-01-16 16:45:52', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R32] {'review_id': 'KMOzaeTzyL36BmmyRdtjcA', 'user_id': 'VD7zLU349znfTsOQtIjVYw', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "FANTASTIC.  That sums it up.   I'm a South Philly Italian born and raised and a hard marker when it comes to Italian restaurants.  We went there this past Saturday and it was truly a wonderful experience. The atmosphere was very cozy and intimate and the service and food were excellent.   Julio, our waiter, was great - engaging, funny, knowledgeable.  Devin, the host, was attentive and friendly.  And it's BYOB!!!  We will definitely be heading back soon.", 'date': '2020-01-12 20:41:01', 'user': {'name': 'Ilene', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2016-05-07 17:34:15', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.67, 'fans': 0}}
[R33] {'review_id': 'hxCi6AmBztx5JZQBavHTQQ', 'user_id': 'ws5xN4JuudHqRLYleWw_1g', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Fantastic food in a really cute atmosphere, and the fact that it's BYO is a huge plus. The gnocchi were outstanding and unlike any ive ever had (they're huge). The grilled squid was also excellent. Highly recommend coming here - it's tiny and intimate so makes for a perfect date night spot!", 'date': '2019-12-02 20:39:08', 'user': {'name': 'Jacklin', 'review_count': 236, 'yelping_since': '2014-09-21 15:04:11', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.19, 'fans': 30}}
[R34] {'review_id': 'QRYRf2_4CEbTTv9_NQajnQ', 'user_id': '_raphVZJb2s51GPw5vIDmA', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Amazing espresso cookie a la mode dessert. The wait staff calls it "hot & cold" dessert.  It\'s a must have. "Nonna\'s Sunday Dinner" is just like she used to make. This restaurant is high class all arou', 'date': '2019-10-29 22:17:05', 'user': {'name': 'Denis', 'review_count': 21, 'yelping_since': '2012-12-12 20:50:01', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.79, 'fans': 1}}
[R35] {'review_id': 'lMdZ0rlIQELKLcOFIziTcQ', 'user_id': '89w_jo0YTnlf4dfGmRMbJg', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Came to Ristorante Aroma for dinner on 10/18. We had reservations for 8 pm and arrived 10 minutes early. We were seated immediately and greeted graciously at the door. We were a little skeptical how our experience would be due to the size of the restaurant, and the tight space, however at first bite of our appetizer, all doubt was gone. The calamari was delicious. Big, and plenty to share. For dinner I had the Tortelloni pasta with Mushrooms and it was delicious. Very much a comfort food because every bite was better than the first. My better half had the Gnocchi with lobster in a tomato cream and that was a close second to my pasta dish because it was equally as delicious. For dessert I had the Tiramisu and without a doubt it was one of the best I've had in Philly! Light, filling without being overwhelming and delicious. He had the Chocolate cake and ate every last bite of it, which is not common, so it must have been good. This place has us extremely impressed, and we are already planning our next date night back. I have not one bad thing to say, because from start to finish, this restaurant was on point across the board. Thanks Ristorante Aroma, we will be back soon!", 'date': '2019-10-20 15:52:05', 'user': {'name': 'Stacie', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2019-10-20 15:52:03', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R36] {'review_id': 'XGFKzUxfgTBmGyeQk2iSYg', 'user_id': 'i9pHdGTNsm-Uh8dHDwKATw', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I was in a wedding in August and they had their rehearsal dinner here! It was the perfect spot. They shut down the restaurant for our party. We had cocktail hour outside in the little alley way next to the restaurant and the wait staff came around with apps - cheese and rice balls! Everything was delicious. \n\nFor dinner it was like 4 courses. We had a salad and 3 different kinds of pasta, an entree, and dessert! So tasty. I loved everything.\n\nThe staff was so attentive and the service was impeccable. Very cute aesthetic. It's small and cozy. \n\nI recommend this spot for an event and I can't wait to come back try it for dinner!", 'date': '2019-10-14 02:44:07', 'user': {'name': 'Stephanie', 'review_count': 321, 'yelping_since': '2015-04-21 16:07:01', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.84, 'fans': 26}}
[R37] {'review_id': '67DSr9WvfRGSqQ2vJl8NYA', 'user_id': 'BkrymGHiC4UgJgZ3-q0wUQ', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Honestly, If I could give this place more than five stars, I could. Probably one of the best Italian joints in all of Philly. For any travel buffs craving Italian food, this is the place. Would definitely recommend it.', 'date': '2019-10-11 22:04:25', 'user': {'name': 'Jeffrey', 'review_count': 17, 'yelping_since': '2016-06-18 00:03:05', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.22, 'fans': 0}}
[R38] {'review_id': 'DSM7vTwIosR_82Plm4owpg', 'user_id': 'fb9eDPNW21CSbYyOfnnwIQ', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Hurt a Little by Expectations\n\nCame here as a party of three. Service was great. It's obvious servers are top notch and well trained. \n\nI had heard wonderful things about this place and, after reading the reviews, I decided to give this place a shot to show off my city to an out of town friend. The food was really good but if I had to pick a handful of restaurants to show off Philly as a foodie city, I don't think this would fall into that bunch. Suffice it to say, it didn't quite blow me away. \n\nI love the BYOB, as always, and you likely won't be disappointed if you go here and, perhaps, I went on an off night, but just taper expectations a little bit upon your visit.", 'date': '2019-09-29 15:33:48', 'user': {'name': 'Dave', 'review_count': 244, 'yelping_since': '2016-03-02 14:07:19', 'elite': '2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.82, 'fans': 20}}
[R39] {'review_id': '-xBV9kKxavgcX7ZAmJE0mg', 'user_id': 'Gfpt2PppV0m7ISq3O9FkBA', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Such a cute byob! I went here with a whole group of  friends and they did a great job handling the crowd. We shared some appetizers, and the Caprese salad I had was made with fresh local tomatoes. My pasta dish was so good, but the best part was dessert--we had lemon cake and something that was a chocolate brownie-type dish that was incredible. It was a good time!', 'date': '2019-09-23 17:15:51', 'user': {'name': 'Leah', 'review_count': 225, 'yelping_since': '2017-07-28 14:47:15', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.11, 'fans': 8}}
[R40] {'review_id': 'HXfnPiorGysOhRcyMMYFYg', 'user_id': 'aFyEZ0Iv8ZaNHNULMPgOsw', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I enjoyed my dinner at Ristorante Aroma.  The food we ordered was great!  I had the lobster gnocchi and it was amazing. The gnocchi just melted like butter in your mouth. We also ordered some appetizers and dessert.  They had an appetizer that came in a fried Parmesan cheese bowl, which was delicious.  The "chocolate bomb" dessert we ordered was also absolutely amazing.  I have had better tiramisu at other italian BYOB\'s in the city, but this chocolate dessert was one of the best things I had here.  \n\nMy only complaint was that the restaurant was actually too quiet.  It was virtually empty when we were eating there, so every time we talked it seemed like we were being extremely loud. Maybe it was because of the particular day and time we went, but it was extremely quiet. I would be interested in sitting outside here, too.', 'date': '2019-09-17 20:24:05', 'user': {'name': 'Gloria', 'review_count': 360, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-24 17:12:30', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.33, 'fans': 22}}
[R41] {'review_id': 'PPc5RTGIjiOi_KWIcGZD6A', 'user_id': 'UPZuq_8dfF3RglJPVu0lvg', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "First time here and couldn't have been more of a pleasure. Our server Giulio was warm and welcoming, and very knowledgeable about the menu, letting us know how specific dishes are made. The appetizers and pasta were delicately crafted and delicious. At Julio's recommendation, we order the baked chocolate treat (ask Giulio for the real name!), probably the best dessert I've had in Philly.", 'date': '2019-09-14 02:51:15', 'user': {'name': 'Evan', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2014-08-07 03:06:42', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R42] {'review_id': '5X6irqhGf5shKx5sad8BPg', 'user_id': 's5foWHnYOOOXJbX5NZhxGA', 'business_id': 'JtDZvV3HddxFnNdrwrWh7g', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "What a fantastic experience, came in on a relatively quite night for the first time. Giulio went above and beyond to provide a wonderful experience, his warm personality made us friends by the end of dinner. The food was just delicious and really couldn't go wrong with anything on the menu as most of it is house made. Highly recommend the gnocchi with lobster and the chocolate bar dessert.  They also topped off our experience with home made limoncello on the house.", 'date': '2019-09-14 02:50:24', 'user': {'name': 'Andrew', 'review_count': 5, 'yelping_since': '2019-03-02 21:54:49', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.0, 'fans': 0}}
